People v. McQuade. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. February 10, 1890.)

Argued before Larremore, C. J., and Bookstaver and Bischoff, JJ.

John R. Fellows, for the People. L. A. Gould, for defendant.

No opinion. Motion to vacate judgment entered on forfeited recognizance granted. For former report, see 1 N. Y. Supp. 155.
